        <activity xml:id="activity-AI4rectangularprism">
            <introduction>
                <p>
                    Consider a rectangular prism with a 10 m <m>\times</m> 10 m square base and height 20 m.  Suppose the density of the material in the prism increases with height, following the function <m>\delta(h)=10+h</m> kg/m<m>^3</m>, where <m>h</m> is the height in meters.
                </p>
            </introduction>
            <task>
                <p>If one were to cut this prism, parallel to the base, into 4 pieces with height 5 m, what would the volume of each piece be?</p>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>Consider the piece sitting on top the slice made at height <m>h=5</m>.  Using a density of <m>\delta(5)=15</m>  kg/m<m>^3</m>, and the volume you found, estimate the mass of this piece.</p>
                    <ol label="A">
                        <li><m>500\cdot 5=2500</m> kg.</li>
                        <li><m>500\cdot 15=7500</m> kg.</li>
                        <li><m>500\cdot 15\cdot 5=37500</m> kg.</li>
                    </ol>
            </task>
            <task>
                <p>
                    Is this estimate the actual mass of this piece?
                </p>
            </task>
        </activity>
        
